<span style="font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:36px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''General Description'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}
{{Blurimage|file=fairy.png|caption=A non-colorised image of Level 95.|hovertext=It's time to go...}}
'''Level 95''' appears to be a large, sprawling group of apartment complexes enclosed by a forest characterized by the faint brown tint of the lights emanating from various sources. The moon hangs overhead, trapping the level in a state of constant night.

From the forest the faint chirping of crickets can be heard, however there have been no documented entities; hence, investigations are currently underway to discover what makes this noise. A cool wind whips through the level, which has a cozy room temperature of roughly 20 degrees Celsius. Many of the apartment buildings are locked with no clear method of entry; however, there is one which is open. 

When wanderers enter '''Level 95''', they will notice the chirps of the crickets immediately. It's faint, but can be heard constantly through the entire level. Beyond the forest is an invisible barrier behind which lies [[The Void]], and within it wanderers are able to faintly see a swirling mass of gas, though what the gas is has not been discovered as of now. Additionally, the cricket chirps seem to entrance wanderers, compelling them to enter the forest "to go home", as many of the affected have been heard saying. This effect seems to affect wanderers who have experienced homesickness or a longing to return home more effectively.

If wanderers remain too long within '''Level 95''', the effect of the cricket chirps will grow stronger, up to the point where it is unavoidable. When wanderers are under the influence of this effect, they will start making their way towards the forest. Based on numerous accounts by witnesses, they will seemingly bypass the invisible barrier and walk directly into the swirling fog, never to be seen again. It is advised to wear earplugs or any other sort of device which muffles the sound to ensure the highest possible survival rate. Lastly, although wanderers have been in this level at the same time, many wanderers have stated that they were completely [[Phenomenon 15|alone]], hence this level may have a sort of [[Phenomenon 15|isolation effect]] on certain wanderers.

<span style= "font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:36px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''The Apartment'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}
{{Blurimage|file=Fairy_apartments.webp|caption=The stairwell within the apartment.}}
'''The Apartment''' is the only of the five apartments present that is accessible. Within it, an elevator is present; however, it is nonfunctional. As a result, wanderers are forced to use the stairs to continue upward. Each floor has the same layout of apartments, with lamps hanging overhead, all radiating the same brown light; however, the light is more intense and emits considerable heat, causing the apartments to heat up to roughly 30 degrees Celsius (86 degrees Fahrenheit). 

Each apartment contains a living room, kitchen, bedroom, and bathroom. The refrigerator in the kitchen seems to have a constant supply of [[Object 1|Almond Water]], which refills every time a wanderer closes the fridge door. The bed itself is extremely soft and compels wanderers to stay on the level for an extended period, making them more susceptible to the effects of the cricket chirps. Hence, it is not advised to come into contact with the beds.

On the roof of the building is a pool which is filled with water that never evaporates. Further testing of the water has discovered it to be [[Object 1|Almond Water]], and wanderers can use this source to refill their bottles. The water never seems to run out and is a reliable source to collect Almond Water. '''Please do not swim in this pool''', as it may cause contamination and dirty the water. Lastly, windows in the apartment always overlook the forest, even if the building's orientation does not allow it. Simply looking at the forest from the apartment is enough to heighten the effect and desire to walk into it, so it is unwise to peer out of any windows int is unadvised to peer out any windows within the apartment.

<span style= "font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:36px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''The Forest'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}
{{Blurimage|file=fairybg.png|caption=The Forest.}}
'''The Forest''' is the most unexplored portion of this level, due to the dangers that it entails. What is known so far is that the forest circles around all the apartment complexes, forming a thick ring. Beyond this, the void along with hazy mist are separated from the forest by an invisible barrier, which is inaccessible to anyone other than those under the influence of the cricket chirps. There appears to be a path within the forest; however, it is known to shift locations at random intervals. As wanderers venture deeper into the forest, the sound of the crickets grows louder, eventually drowning out most other sounds.

As wanderers continue venturing into the woods, they feel compelled to go straight ahead, running towards the barrier and into the void, where they are consumed by the fog. Many of the affected wanderers often claim reciting a strange poem of unknown origin, which has been included. The only known way of reverting the effects of the chirps is to knock the affected wanderer unconscious and safely carry them out of the level, at which point they would be fine after they awaken, and they claim to have no recollection of the level as a whole. 

<span style= "font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:36px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''Colonies and Bases'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}
Due to the effect '''Level 95''' has on wanderers, bases are unable to be established.

<span style= "font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:36px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''Entrances and Exits'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}

<span style="font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:24px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''Entrances'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}
*Falling from the roof of any building in [[Level 11]] has a high chance of bringing wanderers here as they carry enough momentum to enter, though it is unadvised to do so.
<span style= "font-family:Cormorant Upright; text-shadow: 1.5px 1.5px 0px #000000, 1px 1px 10px #45392d, 0px 0px 1px #000000; font-size:24px; color:#4d3b0d"><center>'''Exits'''</center></span>
{{Underline|705232}}
*No-clipping into the floor will send wanderers to [[Level 0]].
*Sleeping inside of the apartment will send wanderers to [[Level 204]].
*Walking deep into the forest '''may''' have a chance to bring wanderers to [[Level 994]].
*Noclipping through a kitchen-like area inside one of the apartments will lead one to [[Level 98]]. This is the safest and most recommended exit.
*As stated previously, being under the influence of the chirps and walking into [[The Void]] would ''most likely'' bring one out of the level, but wanderers should never do so.
